  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="KT51-kilavi">varaivu nīṭṭittaviṭattu āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaṭkut tōḻi varaivu malivu kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">The confidante talking about the prospect of marriage to HER who didn't have the strength [anymore] when [he] delayed marriage.</p>
          </div>



        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="KT51">
<l>                kūṉmuṇ muṇṭakak kūrmpaṉi māmalar</l>
<l>                nūlaṟu muttiṟ kāloṭu pāṟit</l>
<l>                tuṟaitoṟum parikkun tūmaṇaṟ cērppaṉai</l>
<l>                yāṉuṅ kātaleṉ yāyunaṉi veyya</l>
<l>                ḷentaiyuṅ koṭīiyar vēṇṭu</l>
<l>                mampa lūru mavaṉoṭu moḻimē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
             <l rend="indent">The man from the coast of pure sands spreading in every ghat</l>
             <l rend="indent">where the full dewy big blossoms of the curvy-thorned Muṇṭakam</l>
             <l rend="indent">are scattered by the wind like pearls from a broken thread,</l>
             <l>him I love and mother has warmed [to him]</l>
             <l>and father must give [him to me]<note place="foot">Also possible is a transitive rendering of <term xml:lang="ta">vēṇṭum</term>: "and my father wants to give ...".</note></l>
             <l>and even the prattling village speaks for him.</l>
             <lg type="alternate" resp="#TVG" sameAs="6b">
              <l>and even the village talks about [my connection] with him.</l>
             </lg>


                </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
